com.siperian.sif.message

Class SiperianObjectType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class SiperianObjectType
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Siperian object type exposed through SIF request and response.

    There is a predefined, distinct set of SiperianObjectType objects. Each object is static and has a String type name which is the same as the object name. For example, the type name for BASE_OBJECT is "BASE_OBJECT".

    SiperianObjectUid

    A SiperianObjectUid is a String representation of a Siperian object and is comprised of:
    1. Siperian object type
    2. UID_SEPARATOR
    3. Siperian object name
    4. UID_DELIMITER
    5. Siperian object child name

    For example, the SiperianObjectUID for a base object with physical name C_PARTY would be BASE_OBJECT.C_PARTY

    See Also:
    SiperianRequest, SiperianResponse, Serialized Form

      • getSiperianObjectName

        public static String getSiperianObjectName(String uidOrName,
                                           SiperianObjectType requiredType)
        Returns the Siperian object name from a Siperian object UID or object name of a specific SiperianObjectType.

        The name can be simple or a fully qualified Siperian object UID. If fully qualified it must match the specfified type.

        Parameters:
        uidOrName - object UID or name; gets trimmed
        requiredType - when provided with an object UID, the requiredType must match the SiperianObjectType of the UID; a SipRuntimeException is thrown otherwise.
        Returns:
        uidOrName if it is not a valid UID; null if uidOrName is null
